==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sphex
<hw>Sphex</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/,
<?/<?/<?/, a wasp.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of sand wasps of the genus <gen>Sphex</gen> and allied genera.
These wasps have the abdomen attached to the thorax by a slender
pedicel. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <cref>Sand wasp</cref>, under
<er>Sand</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sphex fly</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any one of
numerous species of small dipterous flies of the genus <gen>Conops</gen>
and allied genera. The form of the body is similar to that of a
sphex.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sphigmometer</ent>⟦br⟧
